Section 1 – Definitions.

1. Inappropriate-practices, means, but is not limited to, the following instances:
   1.a. Outright copyright infringement, such as copying material and changing the name.
   1.b. Using licensed material for directed towards commercial advantage or 
        monetary compensation intended without any modification to licensed material.
   1.c. Modifying the material to contain hidden harmful content.
   1.d  Using licensed material or works/services for directed towards commercial 
        advantage or monetary compensation intended without acknowledging or 
        showing appreciation for the creators of the original material it be 
        considered inappropriate-practices.
        
2. Adapted Material, means material is derived from or based upon the licensed 
   material and in which the licensed material is translated, altered, arranged, 
   transformed, or otherwise modified. Not include exact copies of the material.
   
Section 2 – License Conditions.

Redistribution and use in source and binary forms, with or without
modification, are permitted provided that the following conditions are met:

1. Redistributions of source code must retain the above copyright notice, this
   list of conditions, the following disclaimer and definitions.

2. Redistributions in binary form must reproduce the above copyright notice,
   this list of conditions, the following disclaimer and definitions in 
   the documentation and/or other materials provided with the distribution.
   
3. The redistribution and use of source and binary forms, either in whole or 
   in part, must not involve any inappropriate-practices.
   
4. Redistribution for Adapted Material must be available in a public compressed or archival 
   form which include; source code of Adapted Material, all modules it contains,
   any associated interface definition files, scripts used to control compilation 
   and installation of executable code and provided the appropriate decompression 
   or de-archiving software widely available for no charge.


